\subsection{Impact Assessment: Polynomial Elasticity Fitting}
Unlike static models, we calibrated the trade elasticity $\epsilon_t$ using empirical data from the 2018-2019 Trade War.

\subsubsection{Elasticity Extraction}
We calculated the realized elasticity for each month during the 2018 trade conflict:
\begin{equation}
    \epsilon_{real} = \frac{\%\Delta \text{Import}}{\%\Delta \text{Tariff}}
\end{equation}
To capture the nonlinear adjustment path, we fitted a 5th-degree polynomial to the observed elasticity sequence (see Figure \ref{fig:elasticity}).

