\subsection{Revenue Forecast under Tariff Shock}
We simulated the import volume $V_{shock}$ under the proposed reciprocal tariff policy ($\tau_{new} \approx 18\%$). The shock transmission is modeled as:
\begin{equation}
    V_{shock}(t) = V_{base}(t) \times [1 + \epsilon(t) \cdot \Delta \tau]
\end{equation}
where $\epsilon(t)$ incorporates the polynomial trend, Gaussian noise ($\sigma=0.09$), and a long-term decay factor to prevent divergence.

