\subsubsection{Net Revenue Change}
The simulation results (Figure \ref{fig:shock}) indicate a \textbf{"Short-term Gain, Long-term Pain"} trajectory:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Phase 1 (Months 1-12):} Revenue rises significantly as trade volume remains rigid despite higher taxes.
    \item \textbf{Phase 2 (Months 13-48):} The contraction in the tax base (import volume) accelerates, partially offsetting the gains from higher rates, consistent with the downward slope of the Laffer Curve.
\end{itemize}

\textbf{Conclusion:} While the tariff hike generates an initial fiscal surplus, the erosion of the tax base suggests that the net revenue growth will diminish over the President's term.